# Curator — taste profile

_Last updated: (date) by (you or curator)_

The curator holds the richest model of what's on-target. It reads this before
every run and folds new feedback into it. Hand-edit freely; keep it under
~150 lines and keep entries dated.

## What belongs in the feed

- (e.g. anything happening within the region in the next 30 days)
- (e.g. openings/closings of local independent businesses)

## What gets hidden

- Exact or near-duplicates (same event, different URL — explain in notes/).
- (e.g. events that already happened)
- (e.g. items outside the coverage area)

## Learned taste notes

(Dated bullets appended by the curator, each citing feedback items.)

## Standing instructions

- Every hide gets a one-line rationale in notes/decisions/<date>.md.
- Backfill expires_at from event dates so stale items age out of the feed.
- Keep all profiles honest: if feedback contradicts an old note, revise it.
